<!DOCTYPE concept PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Concept//EN" "concept.dtd">
<concept id="concept_rng_qym_qr">
 <title>Data Collector Environment Configuration</title>
 <conbody>
    <p><indexterm>Data Collector
        environment<indexterm>configuring</indexterm></indexterm><indexterm>sdc-env.sh
          file<indexterm>configuring</indexterm></indexterm><indexterm>sdcd-env.sh
          file<indexterm>configuring</indexterm></indexterm><ph
        conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"/> provides
      two environment configuration files:<ul
        conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/ul-SDCenvfiles"
        id="ul_dmt_cfc_1cb">
        <li/>
      </ul></p>
    <p>Use a text editor to edit the appropriate environment configuration file. Some of the
      environment variables in the <codeph>sdc-env.sh</codeph> file are commented out and do not
      reflect the default values. Be sure to uncomment the line when you change a variable
      value.</p>
    <p>After you edit the file, restart <ph
        conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"/> to enable
      the changes. </p>
    <p>Modify the <ph
        conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"/>
      environment configuration files to customize the following areas:<ul id="ul_ulw_sjr_3v">
        <li><ph conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"/>
          directories</li>
        <li>User and group used to start <ph
            conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"/> as a
          service</li>
        <li>Java configuration options</li>
        <li>Java Security Manager that restricts the runtime permissions of user libraries</li>
        <li>Path to JAR files to be added to the root classloader</li>
        <li>Heap dump creation and file location</li>
      </ul></p>
    <p> </p>
  </conbody>
</concept>
